gomodel:SYNGO_4611  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099026 replaced by GO:0042734" , "Rationale: Figures 11 and 12 show localization at pre- and post-synaptic membranes using immunogold labeling of adult and developing brain. Note that authors refer to limbic system-associated membrane protein as \"LAMP\" (current gene symbol is \"LSAMP\").\n\n\"lmmunocytochemical analysis at the ultra-structural level reveals that LAMP immunoreactivity is exhibited by neurons in a stereotyped pattern throughout limbic system areas. Glial cells are not immunoreactive.\n\nIn the adult, LAMP-immunoreactive membrane patches are present exclusively postsynaptically on neuronal somata and dendrites. Myelinated and unmyelinated axons are not stained in any brain region examined.\n\nAnalysis of LAMP expression in the developing CNS during synaptogenesis demonstrates that LAMP is located on growing axons and both pre- and postsynaptically at forming terminal complexes.\"\n\nAnnotated as \"anchored component of ... membrane\" based on GPI anchor. Source: \"All members of this subfamily contain three Ig-like domains that share a high degree of homology and are anchored to the plasma membrane by a glycosylphosphatidylinositol moiety\" (GPI anchor) (PMID:12373100).. Experimental description: \"Female Sprague-Dawley albino rats (Holtzman Farm, Madison, WI), housed in a 12-hr light-dark cycle with free access to food and water, were used for the biochemical and anatomical studies.\"\n\nA monoclonal antibody was used, but validation thereof does not make clear exactly which sequence is targeted. Uniprot lists both rat LSAMP isoforms at 37 and 39kDa MW, while authors show blots with 64~68kDa bands (perhaps a homodimer?)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4611" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

